Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Sunday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee has written to U.S. President Bill Clinton expressing his government 's unhappiness over a perceptible shift in Washington 's stand in the current dialogue between the two countries .
The Times of India :
-- India Saturday termed as a " highly unfortunate development " the U.S. action barring 40 Indian entities and their 200 subsidiaries from having any trade and business relations with the U.S.
The Hindu :
-- The 18th India International Trade Fair was opened in New Delhi Saturday by President K. R. Narayanan who urged Indian companies to establish " India " brand and make Indian products competitive in the global market .
The Economic Times :
-- The Indian industry and government are in for major clean up costs as a Supreme Court order last week paves the way for people to seek compensation for land and water contaminated by industrial waste .
